        <briefdescription>
<para>Initialized a memory pool allocator. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>NOTE: This allocator never really frees memory - this allocation scheme should be used in systems that initialize once at the start and can work with fixed memory buffers.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>pool</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>a pointer to the memory pool. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>memory</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>a pointer to the memory region to be used by the pool. MUST NOT be NULL. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>size</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>the number of bytes availabe at <bold>memory</bold>. MUST NOT be zero. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>pointer to the allocator interface.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="memory_8h_1a90830d17a2e79efd7d376803588fad48" kindref="member">mem_alloc()</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="memory_8h_1aa42e1e26c4edb6451b7f1f2f3c87e5c3" kindref="member">mem_free()</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="memory_8h_1ac45d24195a7cd854df0667705f635e7c" kindref="member">mem_size()</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="memory_8h_1ae0dc2b3d76748dbd5b6a8f69da72bc44" kindref="member">mem_capacity()</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
